# 2. Canonical Pydantic Models

## CanonicalTrade

```python
from datetime import datetime
from decimal import Decimal
from uuid import UUID

from pydantic import BaseModel


class CanonicalTrade(BaseModel):
    event_id: UUID

    exchange: str

    symbol: str

    price: Decimal

    quantity: Decimal

    trade_time: datetime
```

---

## CanonicalOrder

```python
class CanonicalOrder(BaseModel):

    order_id: UUID

    exchange: str

    symbol: str

    side: str

    type: str

    price: Decimal

    quantity: Decimal

    status: str
```

---

## CanonicalPosition

```python
class CanonicalPosition(BaseModel):

    position_id: UUID

    symbol: str

    side: str

    quantity: Decimal

    entry_price: Decimal
```

---

## CanonicalBalance

```python
class CanonicalBalance(BaseModel):

    asset: str

    available: Decimal

    locked: Decimal
```

